Package net.objectof.model

Contains interfaces related to network Resources.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Id<T>
    An Id identifies a Resource object.
    Kind<T>
    A Kind is a Faceted Type that models a data value or data structure.
    Locator
    A Locator transforms (resolves) an Id to an URI.
    Package  
    Resource<T>
    A Resource is a Named reference to an object.
    Transaction
    A Transaction provides the interface to resource management for a single package.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Stereotype
    Stereotypes define the elemental types.
    Transaction.Status
    State transitions OPEN -> CLOSED OPEN -> POSTING -> POSTED OPEN -> POSTING -> FAILED POSTED -> CLOSED FAILED -> CLOSED
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    RepositoryException  
    ResourceException
    A ResourceException is thrown when there is an underlying exception related to a computing resource.
